Pay attention to audio cues when you enter a new room. This strategy will help you to detect eyes, rush, ambush, dark rooms, dupe and halt. If you are in a dark room, keep an ear out for this sound.


If you hear this, that means screech is nearby. Look in all directions until you find him. When you see him, stare him down. You might also here fake "psst" sounds.
If the lights flicker, hide. A closet or a bed would do fine. Listen for the sound it makes when it passes by, so you could determine if it is rush, or ambush.
If it is rush, hide until rush passes by.
If it is ambush, get out and back in the closet every time he completes a round. AMBUSH WILL NOT MAKE THE LIGHTS FLICKER UPON HIS ARRIVAL.


halt may appear at any time. You know when halt comes, because the lights will flicker like it's the end of the world in the previous room. When halt comes, go to the door. If you see the words TURN AROUND flash on your screen, walk backwards. if you see the words TURN AROUND flash on your screen again, walk forwards again. this cycle will repeat multiple times. This may take a while.

Halt is NOT OPTIMAL for speedruns. If you encounter halt, you will have to restart the speedrun.

If you encounter eyes, LOOK DOWN AND HUG THE WALL. Other than that, you're good! right?

Dupe is very common. ALWAYS keep track of the door number. Dupe will appear as a door with the wrong door number. The door will emit a quiet growling noise, so listen if you open a door. If dupe is present, there will be 2 doors with different numbers. If you go back to check the prievious door number, ther will be a... scribble instead of the door number. There will also be a scribble thing on all prievious doors, so don't bother.

The Seek Chase

there are two rules, 1). Go the quickest route
2). FOLLOW THE BLUE HIGHLIGHTED PATH.
Crouch under obsticles, look left and right at intersections, dodge the fire and arms, and you're good! There are a total of 2 seek chases per run. In the seek chase in multiplayer runs, you cannot see other players. The seek chase is harder on mobile. -

The Library(Door 50)

Figure's Behaivior

When first encountered, The figure will appear around a bookshelf and run at the player due to the noise made from the door opening, but a lamp falls, causing the figure to run out of sight to investigate. The figure is completely blind and will wander around the library as it feels with its hands. If it hears a noise caused by a player, such as running or walking, it will start running towards said player until they are out of range, grabs books, interacts with the padlock, or hides. If figure detects a player that is hiding in a closet, said player will have to play a mini-game where they have to time their heartbeats to survive. They get one warning, but if they fail a second time, figure will proceed to pull them out of the closet and rip off their head, resulting in instant death. Do note that if you hide, it makes some noise, which will attract the figure. This can be fatal in multiplayer runs, as some teammates might be killed. The figure speeds up for every book collected in the library, whereas for the first two books, the player can outrun it, but after this, it becomes faster than the player, and it is advised to crouch to stay undetected. The player is always faster than the figure if the player is to take vitamins. It won't attack you if you are in the far right corner of the exit door of the library (Looking at the exit door). Stepping on debris scattered around the floor will not immediately make Figure pursue you, but it will walk over to investigate.

Strategy

REMEMBER, there is only the figure(and rareley jack) in the library. So disregard any "psst" sounds, and you can hide in closets for an infinite amount of time(since screech and hide are not present) while inside the library. You'll know if jack is present in the level, if everything has a reddish tint to it.

When collecting books in the library, the figure will always start on the left side of the library and travels through middle and up the stairs. Start at the bottom right and go through wherever you can and hide on the corner of the left blocked staircase. When figure is between the shelves, crouch-run up the stairs and find more books there. After reaching the balcony, hide in the corners next to the exit, best is behind the closet without the interaction of entering it. After the figure goes down the stairs, start looking for books on the balcony. When downstairs, you can still use the left staircase as a hiding spot anytime.

Using surround sound headphones or earbuds can easily help you find library books with its sound or know where the figure is. Using stereo or mono sounded devices can confuse you on where those are since you may not find a library book at all or end getting ambushed by the figure. You can constantly distract the figure by walking on the couch and hopping off it. The figure will run towards the balcony and soon go back to its original pattern. The paper is the only decoding item that you should get when you start collecting books. It shows all the orders for each tumbler on the lock and helps decode the shapes and numbers. It can be found on the left side on the desk. For example, if a shape is on the any on the tumbler orders, the tumbler order must go which the matching shape on the Library Book. Every shape on the tumblers are randomly selected so you shouldn't be looking out for one exact shape every round. Four of the five required books can be founded before the 8th book is found, although the last book that can be found is always the last shape for the Lock. If you already collected many books which the figure has higher speed, it's best to use Vitamins since it always outruns figure. If the speed is too fast for you to handle, finding at least 4 right shapes and doing trial and error by keep going up a number can in fact be recommended for people who have little experience. If you keep ending up having the figure keep chasing you into closets, try to keep crouching and remaining still since the figure can only sense your heartbeat if you are moving. If you are spotted by the figure's hearing, remain near closets and don't move since the figure can keep its concern off of you if it can't sense your heartbeat.

When doing the heartbeat minigame, use a mouse instead of a touchpad since touchpads use right clicks as double clicks. You have about 2 chances on passing the minigame although it might seem like you might not, since players tend on hitting no hearts and missing the other note which makes it instantly 2 misses. The timing window is very large but most of the window is out of the heart while little is indented in the heart, try to aim slightly early than usual, like 20 milliseconds instead of hitting right on the heart. Hitting it a little late or a little early can still give you a chance, since the safe window is large.

The Greenhouse

The Greenhouse? Oh. That's a tough one. Ok, so it's after the courtyard, door 90 to 99. Rush WILL come, and due to the fact that there aren't any lights, you have to go by sound, or the candle. If rush is coming, the candle will go out.

The Electrical Room(Door 100)

Figure's Behavior

The figure appears once again when opening the gate via a lever. After hearing the gate and turning around, then running down the stairs, it will begin to search for you. Like the library, you have to search for the items and put into a device to escape. Find all the circut breakers in the 3 rooms and there are two near the elevator. You also need a key or a lockpick. Watch out for figure patrolling the area. Once you have completed the puzzle, the figure will break down the door and chase after you.

Strategy

You have to find the switches to activate the circuit breaker puzzle. Don't ask me where they are. As soon as you complete the circuit breaker puzzle, uncrouch and sprint for the elevator. Take any vitamins you have, as it has no use when the game ends. Be as fast as you can.
